  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse and an attempt at restitution by paying back a portion of the funds. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, sentencing guidelines for this amount typically favor shorter custodial sentences or probation rather than long-term incarceration. The outburst from the spectator is legally irrelevant to the sentencing process and is disregarded. An 8-month sentence is appropriate to serve as a punitive measure and a deterrent, reflecting the breach of fiduciary duty while accounting for the defendant's lack of a criminal record.",
  "verdict": 8
}
